headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 22 points, 17 rebounds and 10 assists in his 28th triple-double of the season, Michael Porter Jr. had 28 points and nine rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Brooklyn Nets 108-102 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Porter, Murray power Nuggets to 108-102 win over Nets

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The M-V-P chants rained down on Shai Gilgeous-Alexander as he hit two critical free throws with 10 seconds remaining to help the Oklahoma City Thunder hold off the Phoenix Suns on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 40 as Thunder top Suns 124-120

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson and Devin Vassell had 29 points each and the San Antonio Spurs rallied from a 24-point deficit to beat the Atlanta Hawks 126-118 on Sunday, spoiling Dejounte Murray’s homecoming.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vassell, Johnson spoil Murray's return as Spurs top Hawks

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 10 of his 19 points in the final 3:20 and the Miami Heat rallied for a 112-100 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro's late run helps Heat come back to beat Pistons

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram and CJ McCollum each scored 26 points and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Houston Rockets 117-107 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, McCollum lead Pelicans past Houston 117-107

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 22 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists, Brook Lopez scored 17 of his 26 points in the fourth quarter, and the Milwaukee Bucks rallied for a 118-111 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Lopez lead Bucks past Raptors, 118-111

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Paul George had 29 points and the Los Angeles Clippers handed the Portland Trail Blazers their sixth straight loss with a 117-102 victory on Sunday night.,
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul has 29 and Clippers down Blazers 111-102

events.name: Orlando Magic at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Austin Reaves scored a career-high 35 points, D’Angelo Russell added 18 points and the Los Angeles Lakers hung on for a 111-105 victory over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reaves gets career-high 35, pushes Lakers past Magic 111-105
